  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Add-Product</h1>
    <h2>Basic Path</h2>
    <div class="basic-path">
      <ol>
	<li><p>The Inventory Manager selects <a href="View-Products.html">View-Products</a></p></li>
	<li><p>The Inventory Manager selects "Add Product".</p></li>
	<li><p>The software retrieves the available vendors.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software checks that there is at least one vendor. If there is
	     only one vendor the software uses that vendor automatically.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software retrieves the available departments.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software checks that there is at least one department. If there is
	    only one department the software uses that department automatically.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software retrieves the available unit types.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software prompts the Inventory Manager for the product's UPC.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software prompts for the product's description, price per item, cost per
	    ordering unit, par, ordering units, economic ordering unit, vendor,
	    category id, item #, default unit type, primary par, and secondary par.</p></li>
	<li><p>If an EOQ is not entered but an order by units is, then the EOQ is the
	    by default the same values as that of the order by units.</p></li>
	<li><p>The Inventory Manager enters values for the above prompts.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software checks that the UPC is either unique or empty.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software checks that the item number is either unique or empty.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software checks that the UPC is a valid UPC.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software checks that the description is unique and non-empty.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software checks that the order by units is non-empty, positive, integer.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software checks that the par is a non-empty integer, greater than 0.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software checks that the eoq is a non-empty integer, greater than 0.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software checks that the case pack is a non-empty integer, greater
	    than 0.</p></li>
	<li><p>With the entered values, the software creates a new product. </p></li>
	<li><p>The software stores the product persistently.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software updates any listing of products.</p></li>
    </div>
      
    <h2>Alternate Paths</h2>
    <h3>DB Error</h3>
    <h3>No Vendors</h3>
    <h3>No Departments</h3>
    <h3>Invalid Upc</h3>
    <h3>Invalid product information</h3>
  </body>

